# AI-hint: Desktop entry for MiOS Settings — the one unified configuration surface. Launches mios-configurator-launch, which opens the configurator embedded in the MiOS Portal (http://localhost:8640/configure) and falls back to the standalone HTML editor only when the Portal is unreachable. All settings serialise to the mios.toml SSOT (identity, AI models, packages, flatpaks, desktop).
# AI-related: /etc/mios/mios.toml, /usr/libexec/mios/mios-configurator-launch, mios-configurator-launch, http://localhost:8640/configure
[Desktop Entry]
Type=Application
Version=1.0
Name=MiOS Settings
GenericName=System Settings
Comment=One unified surface for every MiOS setting — identity, AI, packages, flatpaks, desktop (writes the mios.toml SSOT)
Exec=/usr/libexec/mios/mios-configurator-launch
Icon=preferences-system
Categories=System;Settings;PackageManager;
Keywords=mios;configurator;system;settings;packages;flatpak;ai;
Terminal=false
StartupNotify=true
StartupWMClass=org.gnome.Epiphany
# WSLg auto-publishes this entry to the Windows Start Menu under
# "<Distro> Apps" when MiOS-DEV is the source distro, so the same
# .desktop file gives Linux GNOME Dock + Activities visibility on a
# deployed MiOS host AND a Windows Start Menu entry on the Win-side
# dev VM. One file, two surfaces.
